CBS Inc &lt;CBS.N> is issuing 400 mln dlrsof convertible debt due April 7, 2002 with a coupon of five pctand priced at par, said Morgan Stanley Ltd as lead manager.    The securities are convertible into shares of CBS at aprice of 200 dlrs per share, which represents a premium of 26.2pct over the company's closing stock price yesterday of 158.50dlrs on the New York Stock Exchange.    The issue is callable in the first three years only if thestock prices rises abouve 130 pct of the conversion level.There is a 1-1/2 pct selling concession and a one pct combinedmanagement and underwriting fee. REUTER&#3;